<br>
So one day, we see EQ and think collectively, hey this would be great, nobody has to GM, or clean up after the mess when everyone leaves depending on who's house we're at this week.  Win-win we all agreed, and began testing out different characters on servers to see what class we each liked and what we thought impression wise of the servers we'd each randomly selected.<br>
<br>
I started on Veeshan with a Mage named Macintoshsux.  Got him to 9th lvl and was proud of his full cloth and staff that I'd scraped together when I came across my first encounter with a GM.  I happened to die and was unable to loot my corpse.  He rudely informed me that he had changed my name because it wasn't in keeping with the genre and I wouldn't be able to loot my corpse and would have to start from scratch (this in the first months of EQ) for gear...I got mad and pointed out that at the time the naming policy said that I would be given notice by a GM if my name was going to be changed, rather than changed just after I died as I realized when scrolling up that my name was changed when I respawned after my death.<br>
<br>
So, I quit that server and decided against a mage since it seemed like a couch-potato class just nuking and letting my pet do all the work.  Spoke with friends who all gave their opinions of their classes and servers and it came that Norfolk was born on Cazic Thule since the majority of the server was from the U.S. where we're all located, and a ton of folks were all PST, which we all were too.  Again, win-win.<br>
<br>
Made my little shaman alt to hang out with coworkers over on Solusek Ro in the Black Isle guild, but just never had the same amount of fun as I did with my paladin, so when the server move came about, I jumped at it thinking, hey cool, now I can get my paladin that I love to play on the same server with my coworkers and a chunk of my friends from Cazic Thule.  Win-win (see a pattern here?).<br>
<br>
That's pretty much it for my story...who's next? <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=23388>Norfolk Peacebringer</a> Crusader<BR>
